Rationale for classification: Classification not possible due to lack of data. The substance can be "Not classified" or classified into "Category 5" based on the available data (rat LD50 of >2,000mg/kg (dermal route)) (RTECS (2006)). If the study is conducted in accordance with OECD Guideline which specifies the upper limit at 2,000mg/kg, it is reasonable to consider the substance to be "Not classified" unless "there arises an urgent concern to human health," because no study is expected to be conducted with larger doses. However, "classification is not possible" since, in this study report, only numerical results are provided and study details are not available (the priority rating for the study is 2).
